Package org.jimmutable.core.fields

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Field
    An interface to represent a member of a StandardImmtuableObject that requires custom code to StandardImmutableObject freeze it.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FieldArrayList<E>
    An implementation of a ArrayList that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldCollection<E>
    An implementation of a Collection that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldConcurrentHashMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a FieldConcurrentHashMap that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldConcurrentHashSet<E>
    An implementation of a Set wrapper around ConcurrentHashMap (Collections.newSetFromMap(java.util.Map)) that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldConcurrentSkipListSet<E>
    An implementation of a ConcurrentSkipListSet that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldHashMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a HashMap that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldHashSet<E>
    An implementation of a HashSet that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldList<E>
    An implementation of a List that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a Collection that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldSet<E>
    An implementation of a Set that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldTreeMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a TreeMap that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
    FieldTreeSet<E>
    An implementation of a TreeSet that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable).
